# Project Rules вАФ Monopoly (иЫЛдїФжіЊеѓєе§ІеѓМзњБ)

## Identity

- Lua 5.5 mini-game running on the Eggy (иЫЛдїФжіЊеѓє) host runtime.
- Clean Architecture, **seven layers + a `foundation/` cross-cutting layer**. Boundaries and physical mapping live in `docs/architecture/boundaries.md` and `docs/architecture/layer-model.md`. Decisions D1вАУD7 in `docs/decisions/0001-seven-layer-with-foundation.md`.
- Default branch is `main`, not `master`. The `swarmforge.conf` keyword `master` here means "the architect runs in the main working directory on whatever branch is currently checked out" вАФ do **not** rename `main` to `master`.

## Hard Rules

- Naming: files and identifiers `snake_case`; class-like tables `CamelCase`.
- **Inside `src/`**, never call `tonumber` or compare `type(x) == "number"`. Use `NumberUtils` from `src.foundation.lang.number`. See `.agents/conventions/coding.md`.
- Eggy `Fixed` parameters take floats вАФ write `30.0`, not `30`. See `.agents/conventions/eggy-types.md`.
- Do not edit anything under `docs/reference/eggy/` (third-party host docs) or `docs/product/design-source/` (xlsx/docx originals).
- `docs/reports/` is generated; never hand-edit. Reports older than 30 days are advisory, not contract.

## Layout (do not invent new top-level dirs)

- `src/` вАФ production code, organized by the seven layers + `foundation/`.
- `spec/` вАФ tests, split into the `behavior` / `contract` / `guards` / `tooling` / `regression` profiles defined in `.busted`.
- `tools/` вАФ quality and refactor tooling.
- `docs/` вАФ architecture / decisions / guides / reports / reference / product. Front-matter is required (`kind` / `status` / `owner` / `last_verified`).
- `.agents/` вАФ agent-only conventions and skills.

## When in doubt

Read the matching row in `.agents/README.md` and follow that document. Do not predict the codebase from this prompt вАФ read the actual files.
